OL,7,FHelene said: "Our occupational
OL,8,Ftherapist has recommended we need a
OL,9,Fnew one. We've got one in the kitchen
OL,10,Fbut it can't be moved, they're such
OL,11,Flarge chairs, they're very heavy,
OL,12,Fthey're wide and we can't get it
OL,13,Fthrough any of the door frames or down
OL,14,Fthe hallway.
OL,16,F"We did have a chair but the strap is
OL,17,Fbroken and she's grown out of it so
OL,18,Fit's just not safe and secure - it
OL,19,Fwould just mean Vivian could spend a
OL,20,Flot more time elsewhere in the home."
